  "text": "Django's CSRF protection is implemented across three key Python modules:\n\n**1. django/middleware/csrf.py (Main Implementation)**\nThe CsrfViewMiddleware class (line 165) is the core component that validates CSRF tokens on POST requests. Key methods and functions include:\n\n- process_view(): Entry point that checks if the request is safe (GET/HEAD/OPTIONS/TRACE) or validates CSRF tokens for unsafe methods\n- _check_token() (line 349): Validates the CSRF token by retrieving the secret and comparing it with the request's token\n- _does_token_match() (line 143): Performs the actual token comparison using constant_time_compare to prevent timing attacks\n- get_token() (line 96): Returns a masked CSRF token for inclusion in forms\n- rotate_token() (line 117): Updates the CSRF token on login for security\n- _mask_cipher_secret() (line 59): Masks the CSRF secret to create a token for DOM use\n- _unmask_cipher_token() (line 71): Unmasking logic to extract the original secret from a masked token\n- _check_token_format() (line 130): Validates token length and allowed characters\n- _add_new_csrf_cookie() (line 84): Generates and stores a new CSRF secret\n\n**2. django/views/decorators/csrf.py (Decorator Implementation)**\nProvides per-view CSRF protection alternatives:\n\n- csrf_protect (line 7): Decorator that applies CsrfViewMiddleware protection to individual views without requiring middleware\n- _EnsureCsrfToken class (line 16): Subclass that makes tokens available without rejecting requests\n- requires_csrf_token (line 22): Decorator for views that need tokens available but without enforcing protection\n- _EnsureCsrfCookie class (line 31): Ensures CSRF cookie is set\n- ensure_csrf_cookie (line 42): Decorator to force cookie generation\n- csrf_exempt (line 50): Marks views as exempt from CSRF protection\n\n**3. django/utils/crypto.py (Timing-Attack Protection)**\nProvides cryptographic utilities:\n\n- constant_time_compare() (line 65): Uses Python's secrets.compare_digest() to perform string comparison in constant time, preventing timing-based attacks on CSRF tokens\n\n**CSRF Validation Chain:**\nThe protection chain flows from middleware to token comparison:\n1. CsrfViewMiddleware.process_view() receives the request\n2. For POST/PUT/DELETE/PATCH requests, _check_token() retrieves the stored CSRF secret\n3. _does_token_match() compares the request's token with the secret\n4. constant_time_compare() from django/utils/crypto.py performs the actual comparison in constant time\n5. If comparison fails, the request is rejected; otherwise, it's accepted\n\nThis implementation prevents CSRF attacks through token validation and timing-attack vulnerabilities through constant-time comparison."
}

